<DocsLayout title="Template Versioning">
  <h1>Template Versioning</h1>
  <p>
    Every change to an encoding template is recorded as an immutable version. This allows you to audit what settings were active when a job ran, roll back to a previous configuration if a change causes problems, and preview changes before applying them to production.
  </p>

  <h2>How Versions Work</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>When you create a template or save changes to an existing one, the Controller stores the full template body as a new version record with a monotonically increasing version number and a timestamp.</li>
    <li>Jobs record the template version at submission time. If you update a template, in-flight and already-submitted jobs continue using the version they were submitted with; the new version only affects jobs submitted after the change.</li>
    <li>Each version is stored indefinitely (subject to the retention policy) and can be retrieved or reverted to at any time.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>API Reference</h2>

  <h3>List Versions</h3>
  <pre><code>GET /api/v1/templates/&#123;id&#125;/versions
Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;

# Response 200 OK:
&#123;
  "template_id": "hevc-4k-hdr",
  "versions": [
    &#123;
      "version": 3,
      "created_at": "2025-06-01T14:00:00Z",
      "created_by": "alice",
      "comment": "Reduced CRF from 20 to 18 for higher quality"
    &#125;,
    &#123;
      "version": 2,
      "created_at": "2025-05-15T09:30:00Z",
      "created_by": "bob",
      "comment": "Added HDR10 metadata passthrough"
    &#125;,
    &#123;
      "version": 1,
      "created_at": "2025-04-01T08:00:00Z",
      "created_by": "alice",
      "comment": "Initial version"
    &#125;
  ]
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h3>Get Specific Version</h3>
  <pre><code>GET /api/v1/templates/&#123;id&#125;/versions/&#123;version&#125;
Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;

# Response 200 OK:
&#123;
  "template_id": "hevc-4k-hdr",
  "version": 2,
  "created_at": "2025-05-15T09:30:00Z",
  "created_by": "bob",
  "comment": "Added HDR10 metadata passthrough",
  "body": &#123;
    "codec": "hevc",
    "crf": 20,
    "preset": "slow",
    "hdr": &#123;
      "enabled": true,
      "transfer": "smpte2084",
      "primaries": "bt2020"
    &#125;,
    "audio": &#123;
      "codec": "aac",
      "bitrate": "192k"
    &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h3>Revert to a Previous Version</h3>
  <pre><code>POST /api/v1/templates/&#123;id&#125;/versions/&#123;version&#125;/revert
Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;
Content-Type: application/json

&#123;
  "comment": "Reverting to v2: CRF 18 caused file size issues"
&#125;

# Response 201 Created:
&#123;
  "template_id": "hevc-4k-hdr",
  "version": 4,
  "reverted_from": 2,
  "created_at": "2025-06-02T10:00:00Z",
  "created_by": "alice",
  "comment": "Reverting to v2: CRF 18 caused file size issues"
&#125;</code></pre>
  <p>
    A revert creates a new version record whose body is a copy of the specified historical version. The original version history is never modified or deleted; the revert is itself recorded as a new version, preserving the full audit trail.
  </p>

  <h2>Template Preview / Dry-Run</h2>
  <p>
    Before saving a template change, you can preview how it would behave against a sample source file using the dry-run endpoint. This runs the template settings through the estimation engine and returns predicted outputs without submitting an actual encoding job.
  </p>
  <pre><code>POST /api/v1/templates/&#123;id&#125;/preview
Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;
Content-Type: application/json

&#123;
  "body": &#123;
    "codec": "hevc",
    "crf": 18,
    "preset": "slow",
    "hdr": &#123; "enabled": true &#125;,
    "audio": &#123; "codec": "aac", "bitrate": "192k" &#125;
  &#125;,
  "sample": &#123;
    "source_duration_seconds": 3600,
    "source_size_bytes": 15728640000,
    "source_codec": "h264",
    "source_resolution": "3840x2160"
  &#125;
&#125;

# Response 200 OK:
&#123;
  "estimated_duration_seconds": 14400,
  "estimated_output_size_bytes": 12884901888,
  "estimated_cost_credits": 144.0,
  "confidence": "medium",
  "warnings": [
    "CRF 18 with preset=slow may produce very large output files at 4K resolution."
  ]
&#125;</code></pre>
  <p>
    The <code>warnings</code> array contains advisory messages generated by the Controller's template linter, such as unusual CRF values, codec/container compatibility notes, or settings that are known to cause problems with specific source formats.
  </p>

  <h2>UI Walkthrough</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Templates</strong> in the main navigation and open a template.</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Version History</strong> tab to see the full list of versions with timestamps, authors, and comments.</li>
    <li>Click any version row to expand the full template body diff against the current version (additions highlighted in green, removals in red).</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Revert to this version</strong> on any historical version row, add an optional comment, and confirm to create a new version with that body.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    When editing a template, the UI shows a <strong>Preview changes</strong> button that calls the dry-run endpoint and displays the estimated output and any warnings inline before you save.
  </p>

  <h2>Retention</h2>
  <p>
    By default, all template versions are retained indefinitely. You can configure a maximum number of versions to retain per template in <code>controller.yaml</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code>templates:
  max_versions_per_template: 50   # 0 = unlimited (default)</code></pre>
  <p>
    When the limit is reached, the oldest versions are pruned automatically. Versions that are referenced by at least one job record are never pruned, regardless of the limit, to ensure full audit traceability.
  </p>

